'''A free homeland and a happy people''' ({{lang-ar|وطن حر وشعب سعيد}} ''{{transl|ar|watanun hurrun wa sha'bun sa'id}}'') is an [[Arab]]ic communist slogan. It was the slogan of the [[Syrian-Lebanese Communist Party]], first adopted at the first conference of the Political Committee of the party (which also put [[Khalid Bakdash]] at the helm of the party).<ref name="MadeianḤāwī1986">{{cite book|author1=Artin Madeian|author2=Jūrj Ḥāwī|title=حياة على المتراس: ذكريات ومشاهدات|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=C-oKAAAAIAAJ|year=1986|publisher=دار الفارابي،}}</ref><ref name="Franzén2011">{{cite book|author=Johan Franzén|title=Red Star Over Iraq: Iraqi Communism Before Saddam|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wJkY9NfFydwC&pg=PA41|year=2011|publisher=Hurst Publishers|isbn=978-1-84904-101-0|page=41}}</ref> The slogan was adopted by the [[Iraqi Communist Party]] at its clandestine first national conference held in March 1944.<ref name="Ismael2008">{{cite book|author=Tareq Y. Ismael|title=The Rise and Fall of the Communist Party of Iraq|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6uAvs4HqVLIC&pg=PA33|year=2008|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-87394-9|pages=33}}</ref><ref name="Thompson2013">{{cite book|author=Elizabeth F. Thompson|title=Justice Interrupted|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=U5y2UkXxyLgC&pg=PA189|date=15 April 2013|publisher=Harvard University Press|isbn=978-0-674-07609-9|page=189}}</ref>

