The '''Economic Stimulus Appropriations Act of 1977''' was a bill signed into law by American president [[Jimmy Carter]] on May 13, 1977.<ref name="Marshall">{{cite web|url=http://www.dol.gov/dol/aboutdol/history/carter-eta.htm|title=The Labor Department in The Carter Administration: A Summary Report — January 14, 1981|last=Marshall|first=Ray|publisher=[[U.S. Department of Labor]]|accessdate=1 December 2013}}</ref> The bill authorized 20.1 billion dollars ($21,100,000,000) in government spending.<ref name="Marshall" />

