'''Laurent Ronde''' was the Crown Jeweller of [[France]] in the early 18th century. His most famous creation was the [[Crown of Louis XV]], which he designed and manufactured and which was used as the [[coronation crown]] at the [[coronation]] of 1722 in [[Reims]].<ref>''Kings as Collectors: Paintings, Sculpture, and Decorative Arts from the Musée Du Louvre'', High Museum of Art, 2006, see also [https://books.google.ie/books?id=QqvpAAAAMAAJ&q=crown+of+louis+XV+ronde&dq=crown+of+louis+XV+ronde&hl=en&sa=X&ei=owaaVOWMK6qy7Qbg_4GgDg&ved=0CCoQ6AEwAg books.google.ie]</ref>

